            {
              "ImageUrl": "step_1_1.jpg",
              "ImageAltText": ""
            },
            {
              "ImageUrl": "step_1_2.jpg",
              "ImageAltText": ""
            },
            {
              "ImageUrl": "step_1_3.jpg",
              "ImageAltText": ""
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "stepDescription": "In a pan, heat around 3/4th of the butter, add cumin seeds and allow it to splutter followed by chopped onions. When the onion turns brown add ginger garlic paste and fry till the raw smell fades which takes about 2 minutes.",
          "stepImages": [
            {
              "ImageUrl": "step_2_1.jpg",
              "ImageAltText": ""
            },
            {
              "ImageUrl": "step_2_2.jpg",
              "ImageAltText": ""
            },
            {
              "ImageUrl": "step_2_3.jpg",
              "ImageAltText": ""
            },
            {
              "ImageUrl": "step_2_4.jpg",
              "ImageAltText": ""
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "stepDescription": "Add chopped tomatoes and bell pepper and cook till tomatoes turn soft. Then add turmeric, chilli powder and pav bhaji masala and fry till the oil starts separating in the pan.",
          "stepImages": [
            {
              "ImageUrl": "step_3_1.jpg",
              "ImageAltText": ""
            },
            {
              "ImageUrl": "step_3_2.jpg",
              "ImageAltText": ""
            },
            {
              "ImageUrl": "step_3_3.jpg",
              "ImageAltText": ""
            },
            {
              "ImageUrl": "step_3_4.jpg",
              "ImageAltText": ""
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "stepDescription": "Next add the mashed potatoes and salt as required to the gravy and cook for8-10 mins on medium flame while stirring continuously. Garnish with freshly chopped coriander leaves.",
          "stepImages": [
            {
              "ImageUrl": "step_4_1.jpg",
